1. FILE COPY AND SYNC

rsync -aAXHv --delete /src/ /dst/
Archive‑mode copy, preserves permissions, ACLs, xattrs, deletes files that vanished from source.

cp -a /src/. /dst/
Simple recursive copy preserving attributes.


2. DISK HEALTH

sudo fsck -f -y /dev/sdXn
Force a filesystem check, auto‑answer “yes” to fixes.

smartctl -a /dev/sdX (part of smartmontools)
Show SMART health data, run self‑tests (smartctl -t long /dev/sdX).


3. SYSTEM INTEGRITY

sudo debsums -s (Debian/SteamOS)
Verify MD5 sums of installed .deb packages.

rpm -Va (Fedora)
Verify all installed RPM packages.


4. PACKAGE INVENTORY

dpkg-query -W -f='${binary:Package} ${Version}\n' > pkglist.txt
List all installed .deb packages.

rpm -qa > pkglist.txt
List all installed RPM packages.


5. PERMISSIONS EXPORT

getfacl -R /path > acls.txt
Recursively dump ACLs.

setfacl --restore=acls.txt
Restore saved ACLs.


6. NETWORK DIAGNOSTICS

ip addr show > ip.txt
Show interfaces, IPs, MACs.

ss -tulnp > sockets.txt
List listening sockets with PIDs.

nmcli dev status > nmcli.txt
NetworkManager device status.


7. PROCESS SNAPSHOT

ps aux > ps.txt
Full process list.


8. BATTERY HEALTH (devices with batteries)

`upower -i $(upower -e
grep BAT)`


9. SECURE DELETE OF FREE SPACE

sudo shred -vzn 0 /dev/sdX (dangerous – wipes whole disk)
Overwrites free space. Use only on a dedicated drive you intend to wipe.


10. SYS INFO

uname -a && lsb_release -a
Kernel + distro details.


11. LOG COLLECTION

journalctl -b > boot.log
Current boot journal.
